C You can prepare them as starter before the main meal. Ingredients Preparation Step 1 Pour two tablespoons of butter into a pan and arrange the wings in a single layer along the bottom. Step 2 In a small bowl, whisk together honey, balsamic vinegar, soy sauce, ground ginger, garlic, onion powder, and black pepper. Step 3 Remove the wings after frying and coat them in the honey mixture before returning them to the pan. Step 4 Whisk together corn starch and water and add to the pan to thicken the soup. Cover the pan and simer over medium heat. Step 5 Serve over fries, rice, pasta or onion rings and enjoy with friends or family. Serve chicken wings immediately with ranch dipping sauce.